==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eery
<hw>Ee"ry</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Scotch, fr. AS. <ets>earh</ets> timid.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Serving to inspire fear, esp. a dread of seeing ghosts;
wild; weird; <as>as, <ex>eerie</ex> stories</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She whose elfin prancer springs⟦br⟧
By night to <qex>eery</qex> warblings.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Affected with fear; affrighted.</def>
<rj><au>Burns.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eerily</ent>⟦br⟧
